+# AUM CRM Import Center Backend + Frontend
+
+## Purpose
+
+Render legacy business files into AUM CRM modules instead of leaving them as disconnected CSV/PDF files.
+
+## Backend
+
+Added schema:
+
+- `import_batches`
+- `import_rows`
+
+Added API route:
+
+- `GET /api/data-imports/history`
+- `GET /api/data-imports/:id/rows`
+- `POST /api/data-imports/preview`
+- `POST /api/data-imports/process`
+- `DELETE /api/data-imports/:id`
+
+Route mount:
+
+```ts
+router.use("/data-imports", authenticate, requireCapability("settings"), dataImportsRouter);
+```
+
+## Frontend
+
+Added page:
+
+- `/admin/imports`
+
+Added sidebar item:
+
+- Admin → Data Imports
+
+## Import mapping
+
+| Source | Target |
+| --- | --- |
+| Clients CSV | clients |
+| Quotation.csv | clients, quotations, quotation_items |
+| Invoices.csv | clients, invoices, payments |
+| Invoice Items CSV | invoice_items |
+| Items.csv | inventory_items |
+| Service Categories CSV | service_categories |
+| Task Board CSV | follow_ups |
+| AumSmart Quotes PDF | import batch marked REVIEW_REQUIRED |
+
+## Operational rule
+
+PDF files should be kept as review evidence or converted to CSV before automated import. CSV files are parsed and inserted into the normalized Supabase tables.
+
+## Apply steps
+
+1. Copy patch files into the same paths.
+2. Run Drizzle push to create `import_batches` and `import_rows`.
+3. Run typecheck/build.
+4. Open `/admin/imports`.
+5. Upload and preview each CSV.
+6. Process imports in this order:
+   - service categories
+   - clients
+   - inventory items
+   - quotations
+   - invoices
+   - invoice items
+   - task board CSV
+   - PDF as review-required evidence
+
+## Verification
+
+```sql
+select source_file_name, source_type, status, total_rows, imported_rows, skipped_rows, error_rows
+from import_batches
+order by created_at desc;
+```
+
